            <div type="general">
               <head>General</head>
               <p>Zrarieh is a Shiite village about 15km North of Tyre in the interior of the 
                   country, district of Sidon, in the Lebanese South Governorate.</p>
               
            </div>
            <div type="researchHistory">
               <head>Research history</head>
               <p><rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:AQ32NEEF">Aro 1978</rs> is a collection of texts in the Zrēriyye dialect, followed by <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:UHMRXPHT">Aro 1979</rs>, 
                   which is a concise description of its grammar. He classifies it as belonging to 
                   the Southern Lebanese <hi rendition="#i">mutawāli</hi> (Shiite) dialects. He also deals with intonation 
                   and notes a change in vowel quality between “Lento” and “Allegro” forms 
                   (pausal and context forms) in word-final syllables, and a shortening of 
                   diphthongs to short vowels in fast speech (<hi rendition="#i">bayt</hi>→ <hi rendition="#i">bat</hi> etc.), as well as suggesting 
                   differences between men’s and women’s speech.</p>
            </div>

            

